Johannesburg’s international airport, OR Tambo, is the only port of entry for direct flights from Asia, it added, saying the measures had been put in place due to the current risk the virus could be imported to South Africa.
 
Meanwhile Egypt’s Cairo airport started screening passengers arriving from China for signs of the new coronavirus outbreak, airport sources said on Thursday.

There are doctors and health monitors in arrival halls equipped with medical devices needed to examine passengers coming from China, the sources said.
--Reuters--